hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I'm in a band pharmaxo.com Yet it is a measure of the acute objectivity maintained in an enterprise shot through with high emotion that when Old Blue’s senescence finally started to affect her breeding performance and other important genes needed to be incorporated into the recovering black robin population, the leader of the project, Don Merton, evacuated this ‘grand old lady’ from her breeding territory on Mangere Island to South East Island. She was last seen there on December 13 1983. Until his own death in 2011 Merton kept the well-worn aluminium band bearing the number B11384 above his mantelpiece.
